  "prompt": "Will meth show in blood test after 3 days?",
  "response": "Methamphetamine (meth) can typically be detected in blood for about 1 to 3 days after use, depending on factors such as the dose taken, frequency of use, metabolism, and individual health. After 3 days, it is less likely to be detectable in a blood test, but it might still be found in other types of tests, such as urine or hair tests, which have longer detection windows.\n\n- **Blood test:** 1-3 days  \n- **Urine test:** 3-5 days (or longer for chronic users)  \n- **Hair test:** Up to 90 days  \n\nIf you're concerned about testing, it's best to consult a medical professional for advice tailored to your situation.",
